<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the fort Zailiysky</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">the fort Zailiysky itself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">which itself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
, as it was then known, became a major stopping point along the track. In 1929, 
